.\" Manpage for ecurl
.TH ecurl 1 "2025-11-12" "ecurl 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ecurl \- Encoded cURL for penetration testing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ecurl
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBecurl\fR is a small POSIX-compatible wrapper around \fBcurl\fR that
applies common encodings (URL, double-URL, HTML, Base64, Unicode) to
injection payloads and offers helper features useful during authorized
penetration testing: session/cookie management, batch payload testing,
tamper hooks, JSON metadata output, and simple history management.

The tool is intended for \fIauthorized security testing only\fR. Always
obtain written permission before testing systems you do not own.

.SH OPTIONS
The options below are the key flags supported by ecurl. Use \fB--help\fR
or run without arguments to see the full, colorized interactive help.

.TP
.B -t, --target <URL>
Set a persistent target URL. Saved to \fI~/.ecurl_target\fR when used.
.TP
.B -u, --url <URL>
One-time target URL (does not persist).
.TP
.B -i, --injection <TEXT>
Payload to encode and send. Required for normal operation.
.TP
.B -c, --count <N>
Number of encoding passes (default: 1).
.TP
.B -X, --method <METHOD>
HTTP method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, ...).
.TP
.B -d, --data <DATA>
POST/PUT data. May be given multiple times.
.TP
.B -H, --header <HEADER>
Custom header. May be given multiple times.
.TP
.B -A, --user-agent <STRING>
Set User-Agent header.
.TP
.B --encode-type <TYPE>
Encoding type: \fIurl\fR (default), \fIdouble\fR, \fIhtml\fR, \fIbase64\fR, \fIunicode\fR.
.TP
.B --payload-file <FILE>
Run batch testing using each line in \fIFILE\fR as a payload.
.TP
.B --json
Emit structured JSON metadata and base64-encoded response body for chaining.
.TP
.B -s, --show
Show the encoded payload without sending the request.
.TP
.B --session <NAME>
Named session for cookie persistence (saved under \fI~/.ecurl_session.<NAME>\fR).
.TP
.B --clear-cookies
Clear stored cookie jar and session files.
.TP
.B --history
Show recent command history (stored in \fI~/.ecurl_history\fR).
.TP
.B --export-config
Export current configuration to a JSON file.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show help and exit.
.TP
.B --version
Show version information and exit.

