.IP
\(bu 8
5  cURL error
.IP
\(bu 8
6  File error

.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.ecurl_target
Persistent target URL (optional).
.TP
.I ~/.ecurl_cookies
Default cookie jar.
.TP
.I ~/.ecurl_session.*
Named session cookie files.
.TP
.I ~/.ecurl_history
Command history and logs of recent invocations.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
If set (non-empty), disables colored output.
.TP
.B PATH
Relies on \fBcurl\fR, \fBperl\fR, and \fBjq\fR being available in PATH.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run a quick URL-encoded injection against a saved target:
.RS
.nf
ecurl -t "https://target.example.com/vuln?id=" 
ecurl -i "1' OR '1'='1"
.fi
.RE
.TP
Run a POST with an encoded payload through an HTTP proxy:
.RS
.nf
ecurl -u "https://target/api?input=" -X POST -d "username=admin" -p http://127.0.0.1:8080 -i "' OR 1=1--"
.fi
.RE
.TP
Show the encoded payload without sending:
.RS
.nf
ecurl -i "<script>alert(1)</script>" -c 2 -s
.fi
.RE

.SH SECURITY AND RESPONSIBILITY
\fBecurl\fR is designed for use in penetration testing and red-team engagements.
Always obtain explicit authorization in writing from the resource owner before
running tests. Misuse of this tool against systems without permission is a
violation of law and ethics.

